ZH: 请你放过他，他并没有恶意。
EN: Please forgive him, he didn't mean any harm.

ZH: 我希望你能够放过我这一次。
EN: I hope you can let me off this once.

ZH: 别再责怪自己了，放过自己吧。
EN: Stop blaming yourself, forgive yourself.

ZH: 只要你肯放过他，他会很感激你的。
EN: If you are willing to forgive him, he will be very grateful.

ZH: 放过别人是一种美德。
EN: Forgiving others is a virtue.

ZH: 他请求你放过他的错误。
EN: He asked you to forgive his mistake.

ZH: 请你原谅我的无礼举止，放过我吧。
EN: Please forgive my rude behavior, let me off.

ZH: 他一再请求将军放过他，可将军却视而不见。
EN: He pleaded with the general to forgive him repeatedly, but the general turned a blind eye.

ZH: 请您看在老师这一份上，放过我吧。
EN: Please, for the sake of our teacher, let me off.

ZH: 只要你肯放过我，我愿意接受任何惩罚。
EN: As long as you are willing to forgive me, I am willing to accept any punishment.

ZH: 他是个好心人，请你放过他。
EN: He is a good person, please forgive him.

ZH: 我们应该学会放过别人的过错。
EN: We should learn to forgive others' mistakes.

ZH: 每个人都有犯错的时候，放过他们吧。
EN: Everyone makes mistakes, forgive them.

ZH: 请你放过他的行为，他只是不懂事。
EN: Please forgive his behavior, he is just immature.

ZH: 老师看在你平时表现好的份上，就放过你这一次。
EN: The teacher will let you off this time because of your good behavior.

ZH: 请你放过他的无知，他真的没有恶意。
EN: Please forgive his ignorance, he really didn't mean any harm.

ZH: 母亲是最慈悲的，她会放过你的错误。
EN: Mothers are the most compassionate, she will forgive your mistakes.

ZH: 放过别人就是放过自己。
EN: Forgiving others is forgiving yourself.

ZH: 不要忘记放过自己，每个人都会出错。
EN: Don't forget to forgive yourself, everyone makes mistakes.

ZH: 希望你能放过他的不忍，毕竟他是个孩子。
EN: I hope you can forgive his impatience, after all, he is just a child.
